cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper deals with comparing different deep neural network models for human visual recognition, specifically for recognizing handwritten digits. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of generative models and discriminative models, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) research. Finally, the paper involves human subjects viewing and judging stimuli, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
